{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17501714","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17501714"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:32:37+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:32:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1780"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1780","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1780"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.36,0.01,0.06,0.51,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1780"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"39122"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1780","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1780"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1780"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"23445"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"349"},{"type":"tags","id":"4959"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7596"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7623"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42399"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"39122","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/39122"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 46-year-old man presents with painless yellowish-white patches on his tongue (Image) which have been present for the last week. He has a 20 pack-year smoking history and drinks three glasses of wine a day. He has recently finished a course of chemoradiotherapy for a T4 lesion of his right tonsil. On scraping the white patch an underlying erythematous mucosa\u00a0is seen.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial treatment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Oral ketoconazole","Cryoablation","Metronidazole","Nystatin oral drops","Wait for spontaneous regression"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis is an example of oral candidiasis\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cem\u003Eaka \u003C/em\u003Eoral thrush. It is a condition caused by a fungus, \u003Cem\u003Ecandida albicans\u003C/em\u003E, which is a normal commensal of mouth, but sometimes in immunocompromised states (chemotherapy, prolonged antibiotic use, diabetes mellitus etc.) it can overgrow and cause symptoms. The first line therapy for mild oral thrush is \u003Cstrong\u003Enystatin oral drops,\u003C/strong\u003E an antifungal. It binds to ergosterol, a major component of the fungal cell membrane, forms pores in the membrane that lead to K\u003Csup\u003E+\u003C/sup\u003E leakage, acidification, and death of the fungus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral ketoconazole \u003C/strong\u003Eis also an antifungal but is used in cases of severe oral candidiasis that are refractory to topical nystatin. It inhibits ergosterol synthesis causing increased fungal cell permeability.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECryoablation\u003C/strong\u003E is a procedure that uses extremely cold gas to freeze and destroy abnormal cells or diseased tissue. It has not been proved to be effective in oral candidiasis. It is used in treatment of leukoplakia, warts, moles, skin tags, some cancers etc.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMetronidazole \u003C/strong\u003Eis an antibiotic and antiprotozoal medication. It has no proven role in candidiasis yet. It Inhibits nucleic acid synthesis by disrupting DNA and causing strand breakage causing its amoebicidal, bactericidal, and trichomonacidal action.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOral candidiasis is not a self-limiting condition, it requires treatment with antifungal so \u003Cstrong\u003Ewaiting for spontaneous regression \u003C/strong\u003Eis not indicated.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The first line therapy for mild oral thrush is topical nystatin"],"references":["Millsop JW, Fazel N. Oral candidiasis. Clin Dermatol. 2016 Jul-Aug;34(4):487-94.","Lewis MAO, Williams DW. Diagnosis and management of oral candidiasis. Br Dent J. 2019 Nov 10;223(9):675-681."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"23445"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1780"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"18257"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"18257","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/18257"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/9ddc3288-cf70-47b7-a874-7d2f72fd4306.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/9ddc3288-cf70-47b7-a874-7d2f72fd4306.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":800,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"23445","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/23445"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-08-26T15:46:50+09:30","updatedAt":"2023-08-26T15:46:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1780"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"39122"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji